      "Note that this would help for https://github.com/neumino/thinky/issues/179 as we currently cannot pass a stream to `do`.\r\n\r\nContext about the issue linked:\r\n```\r\nPosts.getJoin({ comments: function(seq) { return seq.count() } })\r\n```\r\n\r\nBecomes\r\n\r\n```\r\nr.table('posts').merge(function(post) {\r\n    return {\r\n        comments: r.table('comments').getAll(post('id'), {index: 'postId'}).count().coerceTo('ARRAY')\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf streams are automatically coerced, I could just remove the `coerceTo('ARRAY')` and let RethinkDB decide if it needs to cast the stream to an array or not.\r\n"
